<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title name="TechConnect">IRB 1</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>  

<body>
        <div Class="HeadContainer">
            <div class="top1"><h1> <b> IRB 1 </b> <strong class="Pre"> [PRE-OBSERVATION CONFERENCE GUIDE]</strong></h1></div>
    <div class="top1"><h5></h5></div>
    </div>
<br> <br><br>
        <div class="instructions">
        <p> <b>Intructions:</b></p>
        <p ><i><b>*</b>Please review and complete the questions for <b>"Planning for Student Learning".</b>  They are provided as a quide for the pre observation conference and will serve as an agenda</p> 
        <p><b>*</b>Submit the pre-observation conference Outline Form and lesson note <b> a day before observation.</b></p></i> 
    </div>
        <br>
        
        <div class="container">
            
            <form action="feedback.html">
                <p> <i>The planned date and time to visit class: <input type="datetime-local" autofocus  required > </p> <br></i> 
           <br><b>Planning for student learning questions:</b>


                <div class="form-group">
                <label>1. What do you seek to achieve in this lesson?</label>
                    <textarea name="q1" cols="60" rows="7"  placeholder="write what you seek to achieve here!" required></textarea>
                </div>


                <div class="form-group">
                    <label>2. What are the prerequisite knowledge/skills required to accomplish the lesson's goal/objective?</label>
                         <textarea name="q2" cols="60" rows="7" placeholder="write the prerequisite skills here!" required></textarea>                
                        </div>          
                    


                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label>3. What adaptation/accommodation will be made for students who do not have the prerequisite knowlwdge/skills? </label>
                             <textarea name="q3" cols="60" rows="7" placeholder="State adaptions here!"  required></textarea>
                            </div>   <br>



                        <div class="form-group">
                            <label>4. What provision will you make for students who have already grasped the content/topic? </label>
                              <textarea name="q4" cols="60" rows="7" placeholder="write your provision here!"  required></textarea>
                            </div><br>



                            <div class="form-group">
                                <label>5. What strategies will you use to achieve the objectives of the lesson?</label>
                                    <textarea name="q5" cols="60" rows="7" placeholder="Outline strategies here!"  required></textarea>
                                </div><br>


                            <div class="form-group">
                                <label>6. How does the content of this lesson build on what students have already studied?</label>
                                    <textarea name="q6" cols="60" rows="7" placeholder="write answer here!"  required></textarea>
                                </div><br>


                                <div class="form-group">
                                    <label>7. How does the content of this lesson relate to what the students will be learning in the future?</label>
                                        <textarea name="q7" cols="60" rows="7" placeholder="write answer here!"  required></textarea>
                                    </div><br>


                                    <div class="form-group">
                                        <label></label><p>8. Have you addressed the needs (eg.gender, culture, language proficiency, skills level, etc) of this particular group of students?</label>
                                         <textarea name="q8" cols="60" rows="7" placeholder="write answer here!" required></textarea>
                                        </div>                         
                       <div class="btn"><button type="Submit">Submit</button></div> 
                    </form>
                 
        </div>
</body>
</html>